nces, being given more experience than their cap allowed. This bug meant that players could be leveled by groups much faster than we intended. Our policy is still to openly support leveling of friends, but we want to make sure it is happening within reasonable guidelines; hence the change. This change will not effect solo play or standard (i.e. where everyone is within the same level range) grouping at all.&quot; <br><br>The level range is, as several have mentioned, +/- 4 levels until 16, when it becomes the lowest level needs to be 75% of the highest level. There is no hard cap, meaning you don't HAVE to fall into that range, but you need to fall into that range for everyone in the group to get optimized exp. <br><br>Delays for the higher level exp movement kick in when the group baby is outside the range, but that hasn't changed at all. A 25 grouping with a 30 should not be affected at ALL by this change. Neither would a 15 grouping with a 20. A 14 grouping with a 20 should only be slightly affected. A 10 grouping with a 20 would be impacted by this change, but that 10 should still catch up very quickly - or so has been my experience. <br><br>I asked the programmers who work with the code to take another look at the formulas. The change didn't seem to affect the community much, but the uproar in the last few days signals to me the need for another look. <br><br>more on exp patch: I am not trying to be cryptic, honestly - I'm giving you the explanations I am getting from the coders. Also, I used a low level example because that was the group being affected the most - at least, that's the impression I was getting overall from the various threads. It doesn't (or should I say, it shouldn't) change at higher levels. <br><br>As I said, however, we are actively investigating this right now. Please give the guys a chance, this is a lot more complex than looking at a single number and giving you a snappy answer. I will get back to this thread later on, okay? <br> <p><Img src="http://www.vampireathenaeum.org/daoc/pock.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub31.ezboard.com/fforgottengrailkeepersfrm8.showPrevMessage?topicID=97.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub31.ezboard.com/fforgottengrailkeepersfrm8.showNextMessage?topicID=97.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub31.ezboard.com/fforgottengrailkeepersfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=97.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub31.ezboard.com/fforgottengrailkeepersfrm8.emailToFriend?topicID=97.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub31.ezboard.com/fforgottengrailkeepersfrm8.threadControl?topicID=97.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub31.ezboard.com/fforgottengrailkeepersfrm8.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=97.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub31.ezboard.com/fforgottengrailkeepersfrm8.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=97.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub31.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="forgottengrailkeepersfrm8">General Discusssion<option value="forgottengrailkeepersfrm19">The Sword and Key<option value="forgottengrailkeepersfrm6">Marketplace<option value="forgotten